European Benchmark Coal for Next Year Rises as Crude Prices Gain

-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-09-20T11:27:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/european-benchmark-coal-for-next-year-rises-as-crude-prices-gain.html
Benchmark European coal rose as
crude  oil prices  increased.  Thermal coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or
Antwerp with settlement next year increased 40 cents, or 0.3
percent, to $126.60 a metric ton at 11:51 a.m. in London,
according to broker data compiled by Bloomberg.  Oil for October rose 1 percent to $86.53 a barrel in  New
York . Coal tracks oil and stock prices.  Bloomberg tracks data from information supplied by ICAP
Plc, GFI Group Inc., Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group
AG, IHS McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  